// Regression: nexus-zy0e — bootstrap-Rust `nexus build` previously
// rejected a top-level `main` declared `throws { Exn }` (originally
// observed in dvr6.9.2/dvr6.9.3 wasm-alloc/string fixtures), while the
// self-host nxc.wasm accepted it.
//
// Resolved-by-prior: the row-unify fixes in nexus-xhhq (Pass 2 lambda
// scheme expansion of exception groups in `throws`), nexus-wm4w (...),
// and nexus-qrx1 (row subsumption fallback when the caller row admits
// `Exn`) closed the path that previously rejected this shape. This file
// is the minimal positive regression: a `main` with `throws { Exn }`
// that raises a concrete exception.
//
// Compile-only check — `nexus build` must accept this without a
// row-mismatch / row-rejection diagnostic.

let main = fn () -> unit throws { Exn } do
  raise RuntimeError(val: "test")
end
